    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Peel and finely dice the<strong>\u00a0brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span>\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p> <p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mild-haddock-and-tomato-curry/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong>\u00a0basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p> <p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and cover to keep warm\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mild-haddock-and-tomato-curry/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably <span class=\"text-highlight\">non-stick with a matching lid)</span> with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped\u00a0onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>\u00a0and cook for 6-8 min or until softened but not\u00a0browning</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mild-haddock-and-tomato-curry/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>korma curry\u00a0powder</strong>, <strong>chopped\u00a0garlic</strong> and<strong><strong> chopped\u00a0</strong>ginger</strong>\u00a0to the onion and cook for 1 min or until fragrant\u00a0</p> <p>Crumble in\u00a01/2\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong>\u00a0<span class=\"text-highlight\">Knorr</span> vegetable stock\u00a0cube</strong>\u00a0and add the\u00a0<strong>chopped tomatoes</strong></p> <p>Increase the heat to medium<strong>\u00a0</strong>and cook for 3 min or until reduced to a curry-like consistency</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mild-haddock-and-tomato-curry/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once reduced,\u00a0sit the<strong> haddock bites</strong> over the sauce\u00a0</p> <p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until your haddock is cooked through</p> <p>Tip: <span class=\"text-highlight\">Your</span> fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mild-haddock-and-tomato-curry/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>haddock</strong> is cooked, remove the pan from the heat and stir\u00a0the\u00a0<strong>clotted cream\u00a0</strong>through the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>mild</strong>\u00a0<strong>haddock &amp; tomato curry</strong></p> <p>Tip: <span class=\"text-highlight\">Stir</span> gently so that your fish doesn't break apart!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mild-haddock-and-tomato-curry/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Fluff the <strong>cooked</strong>\u00a0<strong>rice </strong>with a fork, add\u00a0a knob of <strong>butter</strong>\u00a0and the <strong>dried dill</strong> and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>buttery dill</strong>\u00a0<strong>rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mild-haddock-and-tomato-curry/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mild haddock &amp; tomato</strong><strong>\u00a0curry</strong> over the <strong>buttery dill\u00a0rice\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
